  <heading>Creditors as competent witnesses.</heading>
  <formerly-cited-as>DC ST 1981 ยง 18-106</formerly-cited-as>
  <text>A mere charge in a will or codicil on the estate of a testator for the payment of debts does not disqualify a creditor from being a competent witness to the will or codicil.</text>
